listings.title: lsd 25 mealate 90
listings.details:
chemical property called stoichiometry, used in balancing chemical equations.

Stoichiometric measurement units are called Moles (M), the total atomic weight of a given chemical compound in grams(g), in this case we're talking LSD freebase, tartaric acid, and maleic acid.

LSD freebase, without an acid compound to make the nice white salt, has a molecular weight of 323.43 grams per mole (g/M), so to make a salt from the freebase we need one molar equivalent of the acid we're using to make a specific salt of LSD, in this case I chose maleic acid over tartaric acid.

Tartaric acid has a molecular weight of 150.087g/M, while maleic acid has a molecular weight of 116.1g/M. To make a salt of LSD you take a mole equivalent of the desired acid salt and react it with the freebase of LSD using a process and then induce crystallization to retrieve the LSD salt, so every 323.32 gram of LSD base requires 150.087 grams of tartaric acid, producing 473.407 grams of LSD tartrate, while 323.43 grams of LSD base requires only 116.1 grams of maleic acid producing 439.53 grams of LSD maleate.

Despite 323.43 gram of LSD producing 473.407 grams of LSD tartrate and only 439.53 grams of LSD maleate, they are quite literally the exact same amount of LSD base still, maleic acid and tartaric acid are not psychoactive and do not contribute to psychoactive effect but do cause differences in weight, with maleic acid being lighter in weight it causes the final salt to be more potent by weight, 7.733% approximately.

Other fun facts, tartaric acid is four carbons in a row, an acid grouping at each end of the chain, and a single hydroxy grouping on each of the middle carbons giving the LSD tartrate salt much better solubility traits than maleic acid, practically the same thing as tartaric acid minus the hydroxy groups in the middle substitute instead with a double bond, drastically reducing the salts ability to dissolve with ease, something the hydroxy groupings present on the tartaric acid provide the bulky LSD molecule.

The tartaric acid's hydroxy groupings increase dissolving traits of the final LSD salt, so breaking a gram of crystal LSD tartrate isn't too difficult for the average person to figure out, they can make their sheets and vials without any issues. The LSD maleate is not only more potent by weight, requiring some math to adjust the dosage level appropriately, but the reduced solubility of the salt demand expert knowledge or the person trying to make sheets and vials from a gram of LSD maleate would pull their hair out staring at crystal not dissolving in the liquid they put it in. The double bond of maleic acid, in tandem with the second acid grouping not bonded to the LSD that hangs free with a negative electric charge, provide a drastically increased shelf life for the LSD as the maleic acid acts as a preferred target to oxygen, UV, and water, protecting the LSD molecule itself and giving the LSD a much more robust defense system when it comes to not losing potency.

Maleic acid LSD salt is superior for blotter paper to insure no potency loss over a long period of time, but you need to know how to break the crystal down before getting started. The tartrate salt is more common, is the standard for dosage charts found online, and is far easier for general consumers to handle without being experts in chemistry to process the crystal into commercial doses

listings.details:
::::: MDMA IS OUR SPECIALTY :::::
::::: ALL ORDERS ARE IN THE POST WITHING 24 HOURS :::::
::::: YOU WILL NOT FIND BETTER QUALITY MDMA IN AUSTRALIA ::::


3,4-METHYLENEDIOXYMETHAMPHETAMINE

MDMA opens heart heart making you feel happy, open, and loving to others and yourself. You lose inhibitions that prevent you from interacting with others. Everything feels good, including the things you touch and the music.

MDMA is usually taken orally or snorted. You can also put it up your butt. It takes approximately 45 minutes to turn on (10 minutes if snorted), peaks around two to three hours in, and then gradually fades away around the fourth hour. 

The come down will begin around 3 or 4 hours after your first dose. Be prepared to potentially feel down, isolated, and anxious. You can compensate for this by being prepared with an environment that caters for your come down. Also, just try and be at peace with what's happening. You're probably going feel bad or disconnected for several hours but it will pass.  

MDMA is a great drug to take with friends or in a safe setting with new people. If the music is good, you can really get your groove on. You can even have important spiritual experiences and personal progress in the correct environment.

Most commonly swallowed or snorted but can also be shelved (rectal).


::::: DURATION OF EFFECTS :::::

Total: 4-6HRS
Onset: 20-90MINS
Peak: 2-3HRS
Come down: 1-2HRS
After effects: 2-72+HRS


::::: SAFER USING :::::

Taking MDMA increases the level of serotonin available in your brain, which is what gives the drug it’s enjoyable effects. Don’t just take fuck loads of MDMA! Too much serotonin available in your brain can be harmful or even fatal -> Serotonin Syndrome. 

1. Use around friends/people you trust and in a safe environment – somewhere you feel comfortable.
2. Remember to eat well before your dose and try and get some grub into you during the trip too, even though you won’t want to eat. 
3. If it’s a hot day be aware of overheating. Try to cool down & chill out regularly. Shade, water on your face and body. 
4. Keep your water intake. 1 cup of water per hour when resting & up to 500ml per hour when dancing or active.
5. If you can get your hands on some electrolytes, that would bee good. For example, Gatorade or Powerade, even a soft drink. 
6. Start low, go slow with redosing. Level yourself up. Don’t send it straight up, especially if you are new. You’ll act like a knob and regret it. 
7. If you take ecstasy on a regular basis, you may be releasing and depleting your serotonin before it has a chance to fully replenish itself. This means you will be operating on lower-than-normal serotonin levels and this can lead to or worsen existing depression symptoms.
8. It is recommended that you leave at the very least 1–2 months between uses. Even 3 months might not be such a bad idea.
9. It is not recommended to use MDMA if you have or are at risk of Heart conditions, Hypertension, High blood pressure, Pre-existing mental health issues, Anxiety and Insomnia. 
10. If you wanna kill yourself, taking MDMA is going to help for about 5 hours, then you’re really going to want to kill yourself! Fucking, call a friend, do some exercise, get some sleep, take your meds, eat a vegetable. Don’t take MDMA if you are suicidal. 

Most common effects: 
Increased energy, Decreased appetite, Dilated pupils, Increased tactile and visual sensitivity, Dry mouth, jaw clenching and teeth grinding, Nausea and vomiting, Restlessness, Increased heart rate, blood pressure, body temperature, Delay or difficulty reaching orgasm, A sense of inner peace and acceptance, Mood lift, euphoria Increased love and empathy, Feelings of comfort, belonging and closeness with others Increased desire to communicate,
Decreased fear, anxiety and insecurities.

Less common effects:
Visual distortions, Involuntary eye wobbles, Erectile dysfunction, Reduced vaginal lubrication, Increased or decreased sexual satisfaction, Headache, Dizziness or loss of balance, Life changing spiritual experiences, Increased emotional sensitivity.


::::: INTERACTIONS :::::

Go to https://drugs.tripsit.me/mdma 

Dangerous
1. αMT: A long-acting psychedelic-empathogen
2. DXM: Commonly found in certain over the counter cough medicines
3. Tramadol: Tramadol and stimulants both increase the risk of seizures
4. MAOIs: MAO-B inhibitors can increase the potency and duration of phenethylamines unpredictably. MAO-A inhibitors with MDMA will lead to hypertensive crises.

Caution
1. DOx: The combined stimulating effects of the two can be uncomfortable. Coming down on the MDMA while the DOx is still active can be quite anxiogenic. 
2. NBOMes
3. 2C-T-x
4. 5-MeO-xxT: Some of the 5-MeO tryptamines are a bit unpredictable and should be mixed with MDMA with care.
5. MXE: There have been reports of risky serotonergic interactions when the two are taken at the same time, but MXE taken to the end of an MDMA experience does not appear to cause the same issues.
6. Cocaine: Cocaine blocks some of the desirable effects of MDMA while increasing the risk of heart attack.
7. Caffeine! Caffiene is not really necessary with MDMA and increases any neurotoxic effects from MDMA
8. Alcohol: Both MDMA and alcohol cause dehydration. Approach this combination with caution, moderation and sufficient hydration. More than a small amount of alcohol will dull the euphoria of MDMA
9. GHB/GBL: Large amounts of GHB/GBL may overwhelm the effects of MDMA on the comedown.

Unsafe
1. PCP. This combination can easily lead to hypermanic states

Low Risk & Increased Effects
1. Mushrooms
2. LSD
3. DMT
4. Mescaline
5. 2C-x
6. Cannabis: Large amounts of cannabis may cause strong and somewhat unpredictable experiences in combination with MDMA. Cannabis should be saved for towards the end of the experience if possible.
7. Ketamine: No unexpected interactions, though likely to increase blood pressure but not an issue with sensible doses. Moving around on high doses of this combination may be ill advised due to risk of physical injury
8. N2O. Nitros. Nangs. 
9. Amphetamines: Amphetamines increase the neurotoxic effects of MDMA

Low Risk & No Increased Effects
1. Opioids

Low Risk & Decreased Effects
1. Benzodiazepines
2. SSRIs


::::: DOSAGE :::::

Check out this site  https://drugs.tripsit.me/mdma

Compensate based upon your weight. Smaller people should have relatively smaller doses. The doses below would be for a person who weighs 80kg. 

Oral	
Light	40-75mg
Common	75-125mg
Strong	125-175mg
Heavy	175mg+

Insufflated/Rectal	
Light	30-70mg
Common	70-120mg
Strong	120-165mg
Heavy	165mg+

::::: TESTING :::::

Roadside Police
MDMA IS tested for in roadside drug tests and is detectable in saliva tests for 24 to 72 hours after use. 

Drug Checking
The only way to really get a precise measurement of the drugs that are in a particular sample is with a FTIR Spectrometer. The only publicly accessible one of these in Australia is at CANtest in Canberra. 

Outside of that we really encourage you to order a reagent testing kit from Bunk Police. 

https://bunkpolice.com/product/mdma-spot-kit-package/

The easiest option is to just purchase some EZ tests. They won’t test for any other drugs in the sample but it will give you some idea of purity. Like Bunk Police you can just order these straight to your house with real name. It is completely legal to do so. 

https://ez-test.com.au/product/ez-test-tube-mdma-purity/

On that note, just as a point of education. When it comes to testing a sample there’s two questions? 1. How pure is this sample? Which means, how much of the drug I want is in there as a percentage? 2. What other drugs are in there? Most, but not all, other drugs that are in your sample will just be fillers or left over from production and generally not harmful to you. 


::::: EROWID :::::

An excellent site for unbiased information on drugs 

https://erowid.org/chemicals/mdma/mdma.shtml

listings.title: Cloud nine - organic Cannabis flowers - slow cure - Private Reserve
listings.details:
characteristics flavor: lightly sweet, fruity, smooth smoke

experience keywords: spacey, relaxing, expansive

characteristics physical keywords: cherry odor, dense, clean

notes:
it's uncommon to find bud these days that has been cured. most has only been dried. curing is like a lost art these days.

what is cannabis curing?
the particulars of the curing process do vary but the purpose is the same: to convert terpene and cannabinoid profiles to their improved counterparts. terpenes are what gives cannabis the odor. cannabinoids are what gives cannabis the high or stone. in general, curing is a time consuming process that places the cannabis buds together and sealed when plenty of moisture is still in there. varied amounts of time are allowed for the buds to stew. venting of the perspired humidity periodically allows the buds to finish drying very slowly, while many chemical processes occur.

why cure the bud?
it is little known that there is more to the cannabis high (or stone) than the strains themselves. old school growers know that cured bud is superior. cannabis has many chemical compounds, a complex array. the cannabinoids which occur as precursors to delta-9 thc, cbd, etc. while the plant is fresh convert to the actives that we know and love when the bud is dry. the curing process has a different result, the cannabinoid profile is different than the same bud that is dried uncured. it's tricky to put words to describe the difference as the result of cannabinoids ingestion is purely subjective. however, i will say that during a side-by-side comparison of the cured buds to uncured buds, i notice the cured buds have a more spacial and almost psychedelic effect when compared to the uncured buds. truly, both the cured and uncured buds have their own character and either may be useful depending on ones mood.
